• Middle Latin: ingeniarius;
• Old French: engignier;
• Middle English: engyneour; and
• French: ingenieur.

• Engineer—an engineer; a maker of engines;
• Enginer—engigner
• Engigner—a deceiver, beguiler, counsener; also an enchanter;
• Engin—an engin, toole, instrument; also understanding, policie, reach of wit; also suttletie, fraud, craft, wiliness, deceit;
and
• Ingenieur—an enginer, engine-maker; fortifier.

